Foreign exchange transactions at the Investors’ and Exporterss (I&E) forex window increased month-on-month (m-o-m) by 9.78 percennt to USD4.49 billion in March 2018 from USD4.09 in February 2018. This is coming as Nigeria’s external reserves have risen to $46.2 billion as at March 28, 2018, according to data from the website of the Central Bank…